comment._content: About 1935.   The pale car on the right hand side looks at least that recent.

comment.author: 53922404@N05
comment._content: The cars on the RHS are a 1925-27 Buick and under the Garage sign I reckon is a 1936 Chev, second car on the LHS is  1927-28 Chev. State Library NSW holds the same photo as Government Printing Office 1 - 24065 dated 1936 which fits with the car on the right of the street. Of course, as always when dating from the cars age, we can only use the newest car in the photo as a guide, the photo could be taken several years later.

comment.author: 27331537@N06
comment._content: Thanks all, I think we can put a c. 1936 date on this photo.

comment.author: 113590875@N04
comment._content: The third School of Arts building (far left) was built in 1934 replacing the second which was destroyed by fire in 1932. Next door to the School of Arts building are vacant lots. Construction on these lots took place in 1936 and 1937. Reports in the Richmond River Express Examiner (11.9.1936 & 29.7.1937) respectively report on one under construction and the other under tender.
